Recursive reverse
Given a string, write a recursive routine to reverse it. For example, given the string 'and, the reversal of the string is 'dna'.

Input Format

A string

Output Format

Reverse of the string

//Code

#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
    char a[30];
    int i=0,j=0,count=0;
    scanf("%s",&a);
    
    count=0;
    for(i=0;a[i]!='\0';i++)
    {
        count++;
    }

    for(j=count-1;j>=0;j--)
    {
        printf("%c",a[j]);
    }
    return 0;
}
